# Introduction
This is example markdown text that can be handled by Pandoc

%% main core

main :- hello( world ).
hello(X):- write('hello '), writeln(X).

:- main.

%%

The code shown in Listing \ref{main} is a simple Prolog program.

%% ex1 example

goodbye(X):- write('goodbye '), writeln(X).

:- goodbye('world ').

%%

The code in Listing \ref{ex1} is another program.

%% ex2 example

hello_again(X):- write('I have returned '), writeln(X).

:- goodbye('everyone ').

%%

And another code chunk in Listing \ref{ex2}.